defaultDiscrimination Law Association – Written evidencedefault&#xa0;
defaultThis submission by the Discrimination Law Association (DLA) relates to Clause 2 of the draft Deregulation Bill.
default&#xa0;
defaultFor the reasons set out below, the DLA does not believe that removal of employment tribunals’ power to make wider recommendations when it has made a finding of discrimination will contribute in any way to reducing the regulatory burden on business. On the contrary, the experience of DLA members suggests that tribunal recommendations, which are intended to assist employers to adopt improved equality practices and thus to avoid future litigation, are often welcomed by employers.  In this brief submission the DLA seeks to assist MPs and Peers to understand what this power of employment tribunals involves and why it should be retained.
