default(b)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultorder the respondent to pay compensation to the complainant;
default(c)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultmake
default an appropriate recommendation.
defaultSection 124(3) states:
default“An appropriate recommendation is a recommendation that within a specified period the respondent takes specified steps for the purpose of obviating, or reducing the adverse effect of any matter to which the proceedings relate –
default(a)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaulton the complainant;
default(b)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaulton
default any other person.”
